<h3 data-start="50" data-end="94">1.1 Semantic substrates and inscriptions</h3>
<p data-start="96" data-end="174">Let <strong data-start="100" data-end="107">Sub</strong> be a category of <em data-start="125" data-end="137">substrates</em> (media that can carry inscriptions):</p>
<ul data-start="176" data-end="365">
<li data-start="176" data-end="260">
<p data-start="178" data-end="260"><strong data-start="178" data-end="189">Objects</strong>: substrates <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span></span></span></span> (paper, neurons, silicon storage, sound waves, etc.)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="261" data-end="365">
<p data-start="263" data-end="365"><strong data-start="263" data-end="276">Morphisms</strong>: physically realizable encodings/transport <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>m</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">u:m\to m'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7519em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7519em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> (copy, transmit, render, store)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="367" data-end="556">For each substrate <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span></span></span></span>, let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Σ</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Sigma_m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Σ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">m</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> be the set (or space) of <strong data-start="435" data-end="451">inscriptions</strong> realizable on <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span></span></span></span> (strings, images, audio patterns, model weights, etc.). We package this as a functor</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Σ</mi><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">u</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">b</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">t</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Sigma : \mathbf{Sub} \to \mathbf{Set}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Σ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sub</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Set</span></span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="604" data-end="740">so that any substrate morphism <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>m</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">u:m\to m'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7519em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7519em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> induces a map <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Σ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>:</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Σ</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>→</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Σ</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Sigma(u):\Sigma_m \to \Sigma_{m'}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">Σ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Σ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">m</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Σ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.328em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">m</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.6828em;"><span style="top: -2.786em; margin-right: 0.0714em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.5em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> (“the same content, re-instantiated”).</p>
<h3 data-start="742" data-end="781">1.2 The category of semantic states</h3>
<p data-start="783" data-end="834">Now define a category <strong data-start="805" data-end="812">Sem</strong> of <em data-start="816" data-end="833">semantic states</em>:</p>
<ul data-start="836" data-end="1105">
<li data-start="836" data-end="935">
<p data-start="838" data-end="935"><strong data-start="838" data-end="849">Objects</strong>: semantic objects <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span></span></span></span> (documents, theories, canons, protocols, memeplex candidates)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="936" data-end="1105">
<p data-start="938" data-end="1105"><strong data-start="938" data-end="951">Morphisms</strong> <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">f:X\to Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10764em;">f</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span></span></span></span>: admissible <strong data-start="977" data-end="1015">meaning-preserving transformations</strong> (translation, paraphrase, commentary, compilation, proof-carrying refactor, lawful remix)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1107" data-end="1227">Key point: SITH lives or dies on what counts as “meaning-preserving.” So we don’t hardcode it; we require <strong data-start="1213" data-end="1226">witnesses</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1229" data-end="1277">Introduce a <em data-start="1241" data-end="1266">typing / proof-carrying</em> structure:</p>
<ul data-start="1279" data-end="1531">
<li data-start="1279" data-end="1414">
<p data-start="1281" data-end="1414">For each morphism <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">f:X\to Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10764em;">f</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span></span></span></span>, attach a certificate <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>π</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\pi(f)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">π</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10764em;">f</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> that <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10764em;">f</span></span></span></span> respects the invariants of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span></span></span></span> that define its identity.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1415" data-end="1531">
<p data-start="1417" data-end="1531">That suggests working in a <strong data-start="1444" data-end="1478">category of structured objects</strong>, e.g. a fibration over a base of “raw inscriptions.”</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1533" data-end="1547">One clean way:</p>
<ul data-start="1549" data-end="1961">
<li data-start="1549" data-end="1706">
<p data-start="1551" data-end="1706">Let <strong data-start="1555" data-end="1562">Ins</strong> be a category whose objects are inscriptions <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi><mo>∈</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Σ</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\sigma \in \Sigma_m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5782em; vertical-align: -0.0391em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">σ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">∈</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">Σ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">m</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> for varying <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span></span></span></span>, and morphisms are substrate-respecting rewrites/copies.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1707" data-end="1961">
<p data-start="1709" data-end="1773">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">I</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">n</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">s</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">p:\mathbf{Sem}\to \mathbf{Ins}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Ins</span></span></span></span></span> be a <strong data-start="1753" data-end="1766">fibration</strong> where:</p>
<ul data-start="1776" data-end="1961">
<li data-start="1776" data-end="1856">
<p data-start="1778" data-end="1856">objects of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathbf{Sem}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span></span></span></span> are inscriptions equipped with semantic structure,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1859" data-end="1961">
<p data-start="1861" data-end="1961">morphisms in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathbf{Sem}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span></span></span></span> are inscription-morphisms plus proof they preserve semantic structure.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1963" data-end="2031">Think: “same bytes” vs “same theorem,” “same audio” vs “same motif.”</p>
<h3 data-start="2033" data-end="2081">1.3 Memeplexes as closure: SITH’s core axiom</h3>
<p data-start="2083" data-end="2187">A <em data-start="2085" data-end="2095">memeplex</em> in SITH is not a single object; it’s a <strong data-start="2135" data-end="2167">self-maintaining subcategory</strong> of transformations.</p>
<p data-start="2189" data-end="2259">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mo>⊆</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}\subseteq \mathbf{Sem}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8193em; vertical-align: -0.136em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">⊆</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span></span></span></span> be a small subcategory with:</p>
<ol data-start="2261" data-end="3200">
<li data-start="2261" data-end="2496">
<p data-start="2264" data-end="2437"><strong data-start="2264" data-end="2286">Generative closure</strong>: there exists a generating set of morphisms <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">G</span></span></span></span> such that every morphism in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span></span></span></span> is a composite of elements of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">G</span></span></span></span> (plus identities).</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">⟨</mo><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy="false">⟩</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathrm{Mor}(\mathcal{M})=\langle G \rangle</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">Mor</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">⟨</span><span class="mord mathnormal">G</span><span class="mclose">⟩</span></span></span></span></span>
</li>
<li data-start="2498" data-end="2891">
<p data-start="2501" data-end="2569"><strong data-start="2501" data-end="2531">Autocatalytic reproduction</strong>: there is an endofunctor (replicator)</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">R:\mathcal{M}\to \mathcal{M}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="2617" data-end="2891">that maps each semantic object to a “new instance” (a copy, a retelling, a compiled artifact, a taught version), and maps each admissible transformation to a corresponding transformation between replicas. This captures “the memeplex propagates its own transformation rules.”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2893" data-end="3200">
<p data-start="2896" data-end="3012"><strong data-start="2896" data-end="2920">Boundary maintenance</strong>: there is a predicate (or classifier) <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05017em;">B</span></span></span></span> defining “inside” vs “outside” transformations:</p>
<ul data-start="3016" data-end="3200">
<li data-start="3016" data-end="3111">
<p data-start="3018" data-end="3111">A wide subcategory <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>⊆</mo><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}^{\mathrm{in}}\subseteq \mathcal{M}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.9665em; vertical-align: -0.136em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8305em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathrm mtight">in</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">⊆</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span></span></span></span> of <em data-start="3091" data-end="3100">allowed</em> morphisms.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3115" data-end="3200">
<p data-start="3117" data-end="3200">Morphisms not in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}^{\mathrm{in}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8305em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8305em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathrm mtight">in</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> are “mutations that break identity.”</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="3202" data-end="3234">This yields a formal definition:</p>
<blockquote data-start="3236" data-end="3558">
<p data-start="3238" data-end="3558"><strong data-start="3238" data-end="3270">SITH Memeplex (categorical):</strong> a pair <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">(\mathcal{M},R)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> where <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span></span></span></span> is a (small) subcategory of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathbf{Sem}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span></span></span></span> that is closed under composition and contains an endofunctor <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span></span></span></span> representing replication, together with a boundary subcategory <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}^{\mathrm{in}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8305em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8305em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathrm mtight">in</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> of identity-preserving morphisms.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 data-start="3560" data-end="3627">1.4 “Alive” = persistent fixed point under open-system dynamics</h3>
<p data-start="3629" data-end="3755">Life needs <em data-start="3640" data-end="3653">environment</em>. Model the environment as an <strong data-start="3683" data-end="3693">action</strong> of an “exposure category” <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathbf{E}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord mathbf">E</span></span></span></span> on <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathbf{Sem}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span></span></span></span>:</p>
<ul data-start="3757" data-end="3934">
<li data-start="3757" data-end="3841">
<p data-start="3759" data-end="3841">Objects of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathbf{E}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord mathbf">E</span></span></span></span>: contexts (audiences, platforms, institutions, channels)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3842" data-end="3934">
<p data-start="3844" data-end="3934">Morphisms: changes of context (migration, censorship, amplification, translation pressure)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3936" data-end="3958">An action is a functor</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="bold">E</mi><mo>×</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">S</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">e</mi><mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\alpha:\mathbf{E}\times \mathbf{Sem}\to \mathbf{Sem}.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0037em;">α</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7694em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord mathbf">E</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">Sem</span></span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="4020" data-end="4144">A memeplex is <em data-start="4034" data-end="4041">alive</em> if it is a <strong data-start="4053" data-end="4077">persistent attractor</strong> under this action: despite perturbations, replication restores it.</p>
<p data-start="4146" data-end="4181">Formally: an “open-system” operator</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>α</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>e</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mo>−</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">F_e := R\circ \alpha(e,-)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">F</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.1389em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">e</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.00773em;">R</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">∘</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0037em;">α</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">e</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">−</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="4214" data-end="4260">for exposure <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>e</mi><mo>∈</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">b</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="bold">E</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">e\in \mathrm{Ob}(\mathbf{E})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5782em; vertical-align: -0.0391em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">e</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">∈</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">Ob</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathbf">E</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span>.</p>
<blockquote data-start="4262" data-end="4537">
<p data-start="4264" data-end="4537"><strong data-start="4264" data-end="4278">Viability:</strong> there exists a nontrivial invariant family <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>∈</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">b</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">X\in \mathrm{Ob}(\mathcal{M})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7224em; vertical-align: -0.0391em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">∈</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">Ob</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> such that <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">F_e(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">F</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.1389em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">e</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> stays in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span></span></span></span> and remains equivalent to <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span></span></span></span> (in a chosen equivalence relation <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo>≃</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\simeq</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4637em;"></span><span class="mrel">≃</span></span></span></span> capturing “same memeplex”) for a range of exposures <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">e</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">e</span></span></span></span>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="4539" data-end="4624">This is the categorical backbone of “self-contained, autocatalytic bundle of traits.”</p>
<hr data-start="4626" data-end="4629">
<h2 data-start="4631" data-end="4666">2) Information geometry for SITH</h2>
<p data-start="4668" data-end="4761">Category theory gives structure; information geometry gives <strong data-start="4728" data-end="4760">rates, thresholds, and walls</strong>.</p>
<h3 data-start="4763" data-end="4812">2.1 Semantic states as a statistical manifold</h3>
<p data-start="4814" data-end="5052">Represent a semantic object <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span></span></span></span> by a family of probability distributions <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>p</mi><mi>θ</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">p_\theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">p</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3361em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> over observations (tokens, claims, motifs, citations, behaviors), parameterized by <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\theta\in\Theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7335em; vertical-align: -0.0391em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">∈</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Θ</span></span></span></span>. Then <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Θ</span></span></span></span> is a <strong data-start="5027" data-end="5051">statistical manifold</strong>.</p>
<ul data-start="5054" data-end="5302">
<li data-start="5054" data-end="5163">
<p data-start="5056" data-end="5163">The <strong data-start="5060" data-end="5089">Fisher information metric</strong> <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>g</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>j</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">g_{ij}(\theta)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0361em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">g</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3117em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.05724em;">ij</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> measures distinguishability of nearby semantic states.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5164" data-end="5302">
<p data-start="5166" data-end="5302">A memeplex corresponds to a region <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">R</mi><mo>⊂</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{R}\subset \Theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7224em; vertical-align: -0.0391em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">R</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">⊂</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Θ</span></span></span></span> plus a stabilizing flow that keeps trajectories inside <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">R</span></span></span></span>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="5304" data-end="5366">2.2 Meaning-preserving transformations as low-length paths</h3>
<p data-start="5368" data-end="5539">A transformation <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">f:X\to Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10764em;">f</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span></span></span></span> induces a map on parameters <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>↦</mo><msup><mi>θ</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\theta\mapsto \theta'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7054em; vertical-align: -0.011em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">↦</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7519em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7519em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>. Define the <strong data-start="5464" data-end="5483">semantic action</strong> of a path <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>γ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\gamma(t)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05556em;">γ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Θ</span></span></span></span> by Fisher length:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">L</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>γ</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mover accent="true"><mi>θ</mi><mo>˙</mo></mover><mi>i</mi></msup><msub><mi>g</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>j</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><mi>θ</mi><mo>˙</mo></mover><mi>j</mi></msup></mrow></msqrt><mtext> </mtext><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{L}(\gamma)=\int \sqrt{\dot\theta^i g_{ij}(\theta)\dot\theta^j}\,dt.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">L</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05556em;">γ</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.2222em; vertical-align: -0.8622em;"></span><span class="mop op-symbol large-op" style="margin-right: 0.44445em; position: relative; top: -0.0011em;">∫</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord sqrt"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.3565em;"><span class="svg-align" style="top: -3.8em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.8em;"></span><span class="mord" style="padding-left: 1em;"><span class="mord"><span class="mord accent"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.9313em;"><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span></span><span style="top: -3.2634em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="accent-body" style="left: -0.0556em;"><span class="mord">˙</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7507em;"><span style="top: -2.989em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">i</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">g</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3117em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.05724em;">ij</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord accent"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.9313em;"><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">θ</span></span><span style="top: -3.2634em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="accent-body" style="left: -0.0556em;"><span class="mord">˙</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7507em;"><span style="top: -2.989em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.05724em;">j</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style="top: -3.3165em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3.8em;"></span><span class="hide-tail" style="min-width: 1.02em; height: 1.88em;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="400em" height="1.88em" viewBox="0 0 400000 1944" preserveAspectRatio="xMinYMin slice"><path d="M983 90
