<h3 data-start="8315" data-end="8379">3.2 Minimal PDE-style dynamics (usable as a prototype model)</h3>
<p data-start="8381" data-end="8437">A compact “first model” consistent with your RSVP style:</p>
<p data-start="8439" data-end="8462"><strong data-start="8439" data-end="8462">Coherence potential</strong></p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">∂</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi></msub><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">∇</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mo>−</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">∇</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mover accent="true"><mi>v</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>α</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>S</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>β</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant="script">R</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\partial_t \Phi
