</li>
<li data-start="12977" data-end="13065">
<p data-start="12980" data-end="13065"><strong data-start="12980" data-end="13008">Verse as minimal closure</strong>: triangulation/redundancy threshold; emergence of agency</p>
</li>
<li data-start="13066" data-end="13189">
<p data-start="13069" data-end="13189"><strong data-start="13069" data-end="13085">Implications</strong>: platforms as habitats; moderation as entropy control; archiving as conservation; AI as substrate shift</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="13191" data-end="13194">
<p data-start="13196" data-end="13300">If you want the next step to be maximally useful, I can write you a <strong data-start="13264" data-end="13283">formal appendix</strong> that introduces:</p>
<ul data-start="13302" data-end="13612" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-start="13302" data-end="13369">
<p data-start="13304" data-end="13369">a precise definition of the memeplex subcategory <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{M}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">M</span></span></span></span>,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="13370" data-end="13529">
<p data-start="13372" data-end="13529">a theorem statement like “SITH viability ⇔ existence of an invariant set <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{A}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span></span></span></span> satisfying <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi><mo>≥</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mtext>eff</mtext></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\lambda\Phi \ge \mu_{\text{eff}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8304em; vertical-align: -0.136em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">λ</span><span class="mord">Φ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">≥</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">μ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3361em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">eff</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>” (with assumptions),</p>
</li>
<li data-start="13530" data-end="13612" data-is-last-node="">
<p data-start="13532" data-end="13612" data-is-last-node="">and a short “RSVP simulation sketch” (discretize <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10903em;">M</span></span></span></span> as a graph of documents).</p>
</li>
