</li>
<li data-start="1518" data-end="1578">
<p data-start="1520" data-end="1578"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span></span></span></span> (entropy): high locally, but <em data-start="1555" data-end="1576">globally functional</em></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1580" data-end="1695">A junk drawer is a <strong data-start="1599" data-end="1642">low-coherence, high-plasticity lifeform</strong> — the semantic equivalent of bacteria or slime mold.</p>
<hr data-start="1697" data-end="1700">
<h2 data-start="1702" data-end="1767">2. Why a Dresser, Filing Cabinet, or Bureau Can Rule an Empire</h2>
<p data-start="1769" data-end="1858">A <strong data-start="1771" data-end="1781">bureau</strong> (the word itself is not accidental) is a <em data-start="1823" data-end="1857">hierarchical coherence amplifier</em>.</p>
<p data-start="1860" data-end="1894">When documents inside drawers are:</p>
<ul data-start="1895" data-end="1972">
<li data-start="1895" data-end="1923">
<p data-start="1897" data-end="1923">symbolically standardized,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1924" data-end="1948">
<p data-start="1926" data-end="1948">hierarchically nested,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1949" data-end="1972">
<p data-start="1951" data-end="1972">normatively enforced,</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1974" data-end="2019">the furniture becomes an <strong data-start="1999" data-end="2018">executive organ</strong>.</p>
<h3 data-start="2021" data-end="2042">The critical move</h3>
<p data-start="2043" data-end="2154">Power does not reside in people.<br data-start="2075" data-end="2078">
Power resides in <strong data-start="2095" data-end="2153">stable symbolic circulation under constrained mutation</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="2156" data-end="2187">A filing cabinet that contains:</p>
<ul data-start="2188" data-end="2259">
<li data-start="2188" data-end="2200">
<p data-start="2190" data-end="2200">tax codes,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2201" data-end="2219">
<p data-start="2203" data-end="2219">land registries,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2220" data-end="2237">
<p data-start="2222" data-end="2237">census records,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2238" data-end="2259">
<p data-start="2240" data-end="2259">procedural manuals,</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2261" data-end="2299"><em data-start="2261" data-end="2298">is already a governing intelligence</em>.</p>
<p data-start="2301" data-end="2315">Humans act as:</p>
<ul data-start="2316" data-end="2373">
<li data-start="2316" data-end="2337">
<p data-start="2318" data-end="2337">metabolic carriers,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2338" data-end="2350">
<p data-start="2340" data-end="2350">actuators,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2351" data-end="2373">
<p data-start="2353" data-end="2373">maintenance enzymes.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2375" data-end="2421">The cabinet persists longer than any official.</p>
<p data-start="2423" data-end="2431">In RSVP:</p>
<ul data-start="2432" data-end="2596">
<li data-start="2432" data-end="2483">
<p data-start="2434" data-end="2483"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Phi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Φ</span></span></span></span>: sharply stratified by drawer and folder</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2484" data-end="2540">
<p data-start="2486" data-end="2540"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mover accent="true"><mi>v</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\vec v</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.714em;"></span><span class="mord accent"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.714em;"><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">v</span></span><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="accent-body" style="left: -0.2077em;"><span class="overlay" style="height: 0.714em; width: 0.471em;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="0.471em" height="0.714em" viewBox="0 0 471 714" preserveAspectRatio="xMinYMin" style="width: 0.471em;"><path d="M377 20c0-5.333 1.833-10 5.5-14S391 0 397 0c4.667 0 8.667 1.667 12 5
