assistant" data-message-id="7970d17e-80ee-44fb-a734-5dcaa8cf8429" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="247">Below is a <strong data-start="11" data-end="75">clean, formal, non-metaphorical operator theory of furniture</strong>, written so it can drop directly into a technical appendix of your SITH / RSVP work. I’ll keep it austere and mathematical, but I’ll flag intuitions so it remains legible.</p>
<p data-start="249" data-end="310">No images, no folksy language—this is <strong data-start="287" data-end="309">semantic mechanics</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="312" data-end="315">
<h1 data-start="317" data-end="382">Furniture as Operators in Substrate-Independent Thinking (SITH)</h1>
<h2 data-start="384" data-end="409">0. Core claim (formal)</h2>
<p data-start="411" data-end="603"><strong data-start="411" data-end="444">Furniture is not a container.</strong><br data-start="444" data-end="447">
Furniture is an <strong data-start="463" data-end="499">operator on semantic state space</strong> that induces persistence, hierarchy, and control by constraining admissible transformations of symbols.</p>
<hr data-start="605" data-end="608">
<h2 data-start="610" data-end="644">1. Semantic configuration space</h2>
<p data-start="646" data-end="650">Let:</p>
<ul data-start="652" data-end="893">
<li data-start="652" data-end="736">
<p data-start="654" data-end="736"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{X}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> = space of inscriptions (documents, artifacts, symbols, records)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="737" data-end="812">
<p data-start="739" data-end="812"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Θ</span></span></span></span> = semantic state manifold (interpretations, meanings, roles)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="813" data-end="893">
<p data-start="815" data-end="893"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>π</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\pi : \mathcal{X} \to \Theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">π</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Θ</span></span></span></span> = interpretation map (possibly many-to-one)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="895" data-end="943">A <em data-start="897" data-end="921">semantic configuration</em> is a finite multiset:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><mo>…</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">}</mo><mo>⊂</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">C = \{x_1, \dots, x_n\} \subset \mathcal{X}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07153em;">C</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">{</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="minner">…</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">n</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">}</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">⊂</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="995" data-end="1062">A <em data-start="997" data-end="1021">living semantic system</em> is a dynamical system on configurations:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="script">D</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>E</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">C(t+1) = \mathcal{D}(C(t), E(t))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07153em;">C</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">D</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07153em;">C</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">))</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="1102" data-end="1170">where <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">E(t)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> is environmental input (users, institutions, shocks).</p>
<hr data-start="1172" data-end="1175">
<h2 data-start="1177" data-end="1207">2. Furniture as an operator</h2>
<p data-start="1209" data-end="1268">Define a <strong data-start="1218" data-end="1240">furniture operator</strong> <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span></span></span></span> as a map:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant="script">P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{F} : \mathcal{P}(\mathcal{X}) \to \mathcal{P}(\mathcal{X})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.08222em;">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.08222em;">P</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="1343" data-end="1409">together with induced constraints on admissible semantic dynamics.</p>
<p data-start="1411" data-end="1485">But crucially, <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span></span></span></span> is <strong data-start="1447" data-end="1464">not arbitrary</strong>. It has <em data-start="1473" data-end="1484">structure</em>.</p>
<hr data-start="1487" data-end="1490">
<h2 data-start="1492" data-end="1546">3. Three defining properties of furniture operators</h2>
<h3 data-start="1548" data-end="1575">(F1) Boundary induction</h3>
<p data-start="1577" data-end="1622">Furniture defines a <strong data-start="1597" data-end="1621">membership predicate</strong>:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>χ</mi><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>→</mo><mo stretchy="false">{</mo><mn>0</mn><mo separator="true">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\chi_{\mathcal{F}} : \mathcal{X} \to \{0,1\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">χ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathcal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">{</span><span class="mord">0</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mclose">}</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="1675" data-end="1688">This induces:</p>
<ul data-start="1689" data-end="1760">
<li data-start="1689" data-end="1724">
<p data-start="1691" data-end="1724">an <strong data-start="1694" data-end="1704">inside</strong> (contained symbols)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1725" data-end="1760">
<p data-start="1727" data-end="1760">an <strong data-start="1730" data-end="1741">outside</strong> (excluded symbols)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1762" data-end="1804">This boundary is <em data-start="1779" data-end="1789">semantic</em>, not physical.</p>
<blockquote data-start="1806" data-end="1868">
<p data-start="1808" data-end="1868">A drawer exists when the system can say “this belongs here.”</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="1870" data-end="1873">
<h3 data-start="1875" data-end="1917">(F2) Restricted morphism set (control)</h3>
<p data-start="1919" data-end="2003">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathrm{End}(\mathcal{X})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">End</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> be all possible transformations of inscriptions.</p>
<p data-start="2005" data-end="2056">Furniture defines a <strong data-start="2025" data-end="2055">restricted morphism monoid</strong>:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi></msub><mo>⊂</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathrm{Mor}_{\mathcal{F}} \subset \mathrm{End}(\mathcal{X})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">Mor</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathcal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">⊂</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">End</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="2125" data-end="2220">Only transformations in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathrm{Mor}_{\mathcal{F}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">Mor</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathcal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> are allowed <em data-start="2194" data-end="2219">while an item is inside</em>.</p>
<p data-start="2222" data-end="2231">Examples:</p>
<ul data-start="2232" data-end="2354">
<li data-start="2232" data-end="2250">
<p data-start="2234" data-end="2250">filing → allowed</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2251" data-end="2289">
<p data-start="2253" data-end="2289">casual reinterpretation → disallowed</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2290" data-end="2325">
<p data-start="2292" data-end="2325">unauthorized removal → disallowed</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2326" data-end="2354">
<p data-start="2328" data-end="2354">formal amendment → allowed</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2356" data-end="2391">This is the <strong data-start="2368" data-end="2390">mechanism of power</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="2393" data-end="2396">
<h3 data-start="2398" data-end="2425">(F3) Entropy modulation</h3>
<p data-start="2427" data-end="2431">Let:</p>
<ul data-start="2432" data-end="2486">
<li data-start="2432" data-end="2486">
<p data-start="2434" data-end="2486"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">S(C)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07153em;">C</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> = semantic entropy of configuration <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07153em;">C</span></span></span></span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2488" data-end="2516">Furniture operators satisfy:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>≤</mo><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>ϵ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">S(\mathcal{F}(C)) \le S(C) + \epsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07153em;">C</span><span class="mclose">))</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">≤</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">S</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07153em;">C</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">ϵ</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="2561" data-end="2625">for small <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>ϵ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\epsilon</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">ϵ</span></span></span></span>, <em data-start="2585" data-end="2624">even under environmental perturbation</em>.</p>
<p data-start="2627" data-end="2641">In many cases:</p>
<ul data-start="2642" data-end="2758">
<li data-start="2642" data-end="2680">
<p data-start="2644" data-end="2680">drawers locally <strong data-start="2660" data-end="2680">increase entropy</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2681" data-end="2712">
<p data-start="2683" data-end="2712">cabinets <strong data-start="2692" data-end="2712">suppress entropy</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2713" data-end="2758">
<p data-start="2715" data-end="2758">hierarchies <strong data-start="2727" data-end="2758">redistribute entropy upward</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2760" data-end="2815">Furniture is therefore an <strong data-start="2786" data-end="2814">entropy-shaping operator</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="2817" data-end="2820">
<h2 data-start="2822" data-end="2859">4. Taxonomy of furniture operators</h2>
<h3 data-start="2861" data-end="2916">4.1 The Junk Drawer Operator <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi><mrow><mi>J</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{F}_{JD}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0993em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.09618em;">J</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">D</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></h3>
<p data-start="2918" data-end="2932"><strong data-start="2918" data-end="2932">Definition</strong></p>
<p data-start="2934" data-end="2967">A junk drawer operator satisfies:</p>
<ul data-start="2968" data-end="3040">
<li data-start="2968" data-end="2983">
<p data-start="2970" data-end="2983">weak boundary</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2984" data-end="3006">
<p data-start="2986" data-end="3006">permissive morphisms</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3007" data-end="3040">
<p data-start="3009" data-end="3040">high internal entropy tolerance</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3042" data-end="3051">Formally:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>J</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow></msub><mo>≈</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mtext>subject&nbsp;to</mtext><mspace width="1em"></mspace><msub><mi>χ</mi><mrow><mi>J</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mtext>&nbsp;iff&nbsp;“potential&nbsp;future&nbsp;relevance”</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathrm{Mor}_{JD} \approx \mathrm{End}(\mathcal{X})
\quad\text{subject to}\quad
\chi_{JD}(x)=1 \text{ iff “potential future relevance”}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">Mor</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.09618em;">J</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">D</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">≈</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathrm">End</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 1em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">subject&nbsp;to</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 1em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">χ</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.09618em;">J</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">D</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;iff&nbsp;“potential&nbsp;future&nbsp;relevance”</span></span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="3195" data-end="3208">RSVP mapping:</p>
<ul data-start="3209" data-end="3287">
<li data-start="3209" data-end="3226">
<p data-start="3211" data-end="3226"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Φ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\Phi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">Φ</span></span></span></span>: low</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3227" data-end="3259">
<p data-start="3229" data-end="3259"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mover accent="true"><mi>v</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\vec v</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.714em;"></span><span class="mord accent"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.714em;"><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">v</span></span><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="accent-body" style="left: -0.2077em;"><span class="overlay" style="height: 0.714em; width: 0.471em;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="0.471em" height="0.714em" viewBox="0 0 471 714" preserveAspectRatio="xMinYMin" style="width: 0.471em;"><path d="M377 20c0-5.333 1.833-10 5.5-14S391 0 397 0c4.667 0 8.667 1.667 12 5
3.333 2.667 6.667 9 10 19 6.667 24.667 20.333 43.667 41 57 7.333 4.667 11
10.667 11 18 0 6-1 10-3 12s-6.667 5-14 9c-28.667 14.667-53.667 35.667-75 63
-1.333 1.333-3.167 3.5-5.5 6.5s-4 4.833-5 5.5c-1 .667-2.5 1.333-4.5 2s-4.333 1
-7 1c-4.667 0-9.167-1.833-13.5-5.5S337 184 337 178c0-12.667 15.667-32.333 47-59
