<hr data-start="308" data-end="311">
<h1 data-start="313" data-end="363">Built Environments as Agency-Extending Operators</h1>
<h2 data-start="365" data-end="392">1. Core thesis (precise)</h2>
<p data-start="394" data-end="598">A home, city, or empire is not merely inhabited by agents; it is a <strong data-start="461" data-end="485">distributed actuator</strong> that externalizes the agency, constraints, and intentions of the biological and social systems that designed it.</p>
<p data-start="600" data-end="748">Under SITH, built environments are <strong data-start="635" data-end="662">living semantic systems</strong> whose function is to <em data-start="684" data-end="747">store, stabilize, and execute intention across time and scale</em>.</p>
<hr data-start="750" data-end="753">
<h2 data-start="755" data-end="794">2. Agency as a field, not a property</h2>
<p data-start="796" data-end="832">Let agency be defined operationally:</p>
<blockquote data-start="834" data-end="945">
<p data-start="836" data-end="945"><strong data-start="836" data-end="846">Agency</strong> is the capacity of a system to bias future state transitions toward a constrained set of outcomes.</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="947" data-end="963">This definition:</p>
<ul data-start="964" data-end="1061">
<li data-start="964" data-end="997">
<p data-start="966" data-end="997">does not require consciousness,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="998" data-end="1025">
<p data-start="1000" data-end="1025">does not require biology,</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1026" data-end="1061">
<p data-start="1028" data-end="1061">does not require central control.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1063" data-end="1177">In RSVP terms, agency is expressed as <strong data-start="1101" data-end="1118">directed flow</strong> in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mover accent="true"><mi>v</mi><mo>⃗</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\vec v</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.714em;"></span><span class="mord accent"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.714em;"><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">v</span></span><span style="top: -3em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="accent-body" style="left: -0.2077em;"><span class="overlay" style="height: 0.714em; width: 0.471em;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="0.471em" height="0.714em" viewBox="0 0 471 714" preserveAspectRatio="xMinYMin" style="width: 0.471em;"><path d="M377 20c0-5.333 1.833-10 5.5-14S391 0 397 0c4.667 0 8.667 1.667 12 5
3.333 2.667 6.667 9 10 19 6.667 24.667 20.333 43.667 41 57 7.333 4.667 11
