<p data-start="1071" data-end="1234">The merge you are proposing is <strong data-start="1102" data-end="1109">not</strong> a reconciliation — it is a <em data-start="1137" data-end="1160">dialectical synthesis</em>, with the draft as thesis and the main version as stabilizing constraint.</p>
<p data-start="1236" data-end="1300">That is exactly the right instinct for a paper of this ambition.</p>
<hr data-start="1302" data-end="1305">
<h2 data-start="1307" data-end="1364">2. Validate Your Proposed Final Structure (It’s Sound)</h2>
<p data-start="1366" data-end="1498">Your proposed structure is coherent and, importantly, <em data-start="1420" data-end="1438">reviewer-legible</em>. A few observations that confirm you’re on the right track:</p>
<ul data-start="1500" data-end="2135">
<li data-start="1500" data-end="1686">
<p data-start="1502" data-end="1557">Using the <strong data-start="1512" data-end="1537">draft as the backbone</strong> is correct because:</p>
