</blockquote>
<p data-start="2420" data-end="2506">This helps reviewers understand that furniture is <em data-start="2470" data-end="2486">representative</em>, not idiosyncratic.</p>
<hr data-start="2508" data-end="2511">
<h2 data-start="2513" data-end="2567">3. The Real Editorial Problem (and How to Solve It)</h2>
<p data-start="2569" data-end="2675">The real challenge in merging these documents is <strong data-start="2618" data-end="2642">not content conflict</strong>, but <strong data-start="2648" data-end="2674">duplication with drift</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="2677" data-end="2711">You have multiple explanations of:</p>
<ul data-start="2713" data-end="2822">
<li data-start="2713" data-end="2738">
<p data-start="2715" data-end="2738">autocatalytic closure</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2739" data-end="2759">
<p data-start="2741" data-end="2759">error thresholds</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2760" data-end="2795">
<p data-start="2762" data-end="2795">minimal closure / triangulation</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2796" data-end="2822">
<p data-start="2798" data-end="2822">substrate independence</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2824" data-end="2912">that are <em data-start="2833" data-end="2848">not identical</em>, but are close enough that naive merging would feel repetitive.</p>
<h3 data-start="2914" data-end="2943">The correct rule is this:</h3>
<blockquote data-start="2945" data-end="3079">
<p data-start="2947" data-end="3079"><strong data-start="2947" data-end="3079">Each core concept gets exactly one “canonical explanation”,<br data-start="3008" data-end="3011">
and all other appearances must either reference it or deepen it.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="3081" data-end="3092">Concretely:</p>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex flex-col-reverse w-fit"><table data-start="3094" data-end="3384" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="3094" data-end="3138"><tr data-start="3094" data-end="3138"><th data-start="3094" data-end="3104" data-col-size="sm">Concept</th><th data-start="3104" data-end="3125" data-col-size="sm">Canonical Location</th><th data-start="3125" data-end="3138" data-col-size="sm">Elsewhere</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="3178" data-end="3384"><tr data-start="3178" data-end="3228"><td data-start="3178" data-end="3202" data-col-size="sm">Autocatalytic closure</td><td data-start="3202" data-end="3214" data-col-size="sm">Section 2</td><td data-start="3214" data-end="3228" data-col-size="sm">Refer back</td></tr><tr data-start="3229" data-end="3276"><td data-start="3229" data-end="3247" data-col-size="sm">Error threshold</td><td data-start="3247" data-end="3259" data-col-size="sm">Section 4</td><td data-start="3259" data-end="3276" data-col-size="sm">Refer + apply</td></tr><tr data-start="3277" data-end="3324"><td data-start="3277" data-end="3295" data-col-size="sm">Minimal closure</td><td data-start="3295" data-end="3307" data-col-size="sm">Section 5</td><td data-start="3307" data-end="3324" data-col-size="sm">Refer + scale</td></tr><tr data-start="3325" data-end="3384"><td data-start="3325" data-end="3350" data-col-size="sm">Substrate independence</td><td data-start="3350" data-end="3370" data-col-size="sm">Section 1.1 + 4.1</td><td data-start="3370" data-end="3384" data-col-size="sm">Refer only</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sticky h-0 select-none end-(--thread-content-margin) self-end"><div class="absolute end-0 flex items-end"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="Copy table" class="hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary text-token-text-secondary my-1 rounded-sm p-1 transition-opacity group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:pointer-events-none group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:opacity-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></span></div></div></div></div>
<p data-start="3386" data-end="3470">This rule alone will reduce perceived redundancy by ~30% without deleting any ideas.</p>
<hr data-start="3472" data-end="3475">
<h2 data-start="3477" data-end="3515">4. Two Execution Modes (Choose One)</h2>
<p data-start="3517" data-end="3558">Here’s where you decide <em data-start="3541" data-end="3546">how</em> we proceed.</p>
<h3 data-start="3560" data-end="3613"><strong data-start="3564" data-end="3613">Mode A — Surgical Merge (Recommended for You)</strong></h3>
<p data-start="3615" data-end="3679">You stay intellectually in control; I act as an editor–engineer.</p>
<p data-start="3681" data-end="3693"><strong data-start="3681" data-end="3693">Process:</strong></p>
<ol data-start="3694" data-end="4070">
<li data-start="3694" data-end="3747">
<p data-start="3697" data-end="3747">I take <strong data-start="3704" data-end="3729">one section at a time</strong> (e.g. Section 1).</p>
